ADA Melissa Inlow appeared for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Poss. Defense is disputing the restitution request.  State called J.J., victim.  Sworn by clerk.  State questioned the witness.  1985 Chevy tool truck.  Victim described the damages done to the truck.  Restitution worksheet shown to the witness and identified.  Worksheet testified to.  Tools also missing.  Attorney Poss cross examined the witness.  Questioned as to where the vehicle was and who had access. Witness never saw defendant damage vehicle or take property.  State redirect.  Defense recross.  Witness made a statement to the court.  No other witnesses.  Defendant does not wish to testify.  State made argument.  Defense made argument.  Defense wants to research abandonment and permission issues.  Court ordered:  restitution in the amount of $7965.61, plus surcharges.
